  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">AMERA-Egypt Asylum Seeker and Refugee Support Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Refugees and asylum-seekers flee to Egypt from countries across Africa and the Middle East seeking protection from persecution, violence and abuse. However, when they arrive in Egypt, the facilities for properly assessing their claims for refugee status and for receiving other forms of psychological and social support are very limited. This often means that refugees and asylum seekers are consigned to the margins of society, unable to fend for themselves and vulnerable to discrimination and abuse. This proposal aims to help refugees arriving in Egypt with their legal applications to ensure that they present their cases in the most accurate way possible. If they are successful, this opens up access to health and education services, and the possibility of staying and working in Egypt legally.</narrative>
  </description>
